When South African seems to be blanketed in doom and pessimism, it gives the heart a little flip to know that, here and there, quiet little miracles are happening which are transforming the lives of the general population. The Ndlovu Wits Audiology (NWA) clinic, run by experts from Wits University, has been doing praiseworthy outreach work in identifying and helping people with hearing disabilities. Hearing is something most of us take for granted but, in this country, hearing problems are the third-most prevalent form of disability, after visual impairment and physical disability. So, the work of the NWA is vital....